FieldHelpers.html.title: FieldHelpers

FieldHelpers.html.summary: Helper methods for rendering field values in pdf reports
FieldHelpers.html.description: This class contains helper methods for working with fields in a form. It is intended to be used in conjunction with the ReportHelpers class.

FieldHelpers.html#choiceBoxes.title: choiceBoxes( input [, val ] )  {string}
FieldHelpers.html#choiceBoxes.name: choiceBoxes
FieldHelpers.html#choiceBoxes.summary: Create list of checkboxes for choicevalues
FieldHelpers.html#choiceBoxes.description: Creates an HTML string from a choice field with a list of checkboxes for choicevalues opts = -hcb -hcb is horizontal choiceboxes, default is vertical choiceboxes.

FieldHelpers.html#customynBox.title: customynBox( input [, val ] )  {string}
FieldHelpers.html#customynBox.name: customynBox
FieldHelpers.html#customynBox.description: get custom yn field as appropriate opt = -syn | -yno | -rdo -syn only first letter of label (or 3 if neutral)

FieldHelpers.html#fldVal.title: fldVal( input [, i ] )  {string}
FieldHelpers.html#fldVal.name: fldVal
FieldHelpers.html#fldVal.description: This function returns the report HTML formatted value of a field. For null values default return is '---'.

FieldHelpers.html#getReportVal.title: getReportVal( [ dn [, mfld [, val ] ] ] )  {*}
FieldHelpers.html#getReportVal.name: getReportVal
FieldHelpers.html#getReportVal.description: Produces the html string of a field value based on its type and options after checking for repeatable values.

FieldHelpers.html#mkMfld.title: mkMfld( dn [, span [, opt ] ] )  {Mfld}
FieldHelpers.html#mkMfld.name: mkMfld
FieldHelpers.html#mkMfld.description: This function creates a Mfld object which possesess most of the properties as a fulcrum field with the addition of: span, opt

FieldHelpers.html#optionIs.title: optionIs( opt, option )  {boolean|null}
FieldHelpers.html#optionIs.name: optionIs
FieldHelpers.html#optionIs.description: Checks if a field option string contains a specific option. Current options supported: -rdo = radio buttons instead of checkboxes -cb = choice boxes (checkboxes) -hcb = horizontal choice boxes -syn = short yes no (first letter only) -yon = yes no only (no neutral option) -na = replace null values with 'N/A' instead of '---' -hn = hide null values (do not display field if value is null)

FieldHelpers.html#.Mfld.title: Mfld
FieldHelpers.html#.Mfld.name: Mfld
FieldHelpers.html#.Mfld.summary: Constructor for Merjent Fulcrum field types
FieldHelpers.html#.Mfld.description: Properties of mFld are the same as Fulcrum field properties, except: 'parent' which is truncated to only the direct parent. 'span' and 'opt' are added to Fulcrum Field properties. With the addtion of the 'span' and 'opt' properties.

FieldHelpers.html#.MfldColl.title: MfldColl
FieldHelpers.html#.MfldColl.name: MfldColl
FieldHelpers.html#.MfldColl.description: It has the same methods as a standard array with the addition of the .m method. New MfldColl is created from mkMfld() method in Field Helpers Class.

FieldHelpers.html#.MfldOpt.title: MfldOpt
FieldHelpers.html#.MfldOpt.name: MfldOpt
FieldHelpers.html#.MfldOpt.description: Options for Mfld to specify drawing of values in Merjent pdf reports. Properties are strings starting with -. ie: '-hcb'. Entire opt property of Mfld is a concatenated string. ie: '-cb-hcb-rdo'

FulcrumHelpers.html#getRepDn.title: getRepDn( dn )  {string}
FulcrumHelpers.html#getRepDn.name: getRepDn

FulcrumHelpers.html#getReportIDvars.title: getReportIDvars( [ reportDate ] )  {Object}
FulcrumHelpers.html#getReportIDvars.name: getReportIDvars
FulcrumHelpers.html#getReportIDvars.description: Get information pieces used to build report id

FulcrumHelpers.html#isMerjentEmail.name: isMerjentEmail
FulcrumHelpers.html#isMerjentEmail.description: Checks if current user email ends in'merjent.com'

FulcrumHelpers.html#makeDnsRow.name: makeDnsRow
FulcrumHelpers.html#makeDnsRow.description: Creates an object from a list of data names. Excludes Labels, Sections and HyperlinkFields.

FulcrumHelpers.html#makeFvDict.name: makeFvDict
FulcrumHelpers.html#makeFvDict.description: Input a fulcrum form schema Object and returns a dictionary object of {data_name:form_value}.

FulcrumHelpers.html#makeRepRows.title: makeRepRows( repeatableDn [, exc ] )  {Array.<Object>}
FulcrumHelpers.html#makeRepRows.name: makeRepRows
FulcrumHelpers.html#makeRepRows.description: Converts a repeatable to an Array of Objects. Input repeatable data name.

FulcrumHelpers.html#photoCheck4Caps.title: photoCheck4Caps( dn )  {boolean}
FulcrumHelpers.html#photoCheck4Caps.name: photoCheck4Caps
FulcrumHelpers.html#photoCheck4Caps.description: Checks photofield for photos without a caption. Returns an Alert.

FulcrumHelpers.html#photoLandscape.title: photoLandscape( event )  {boolean}
FulcrumHelpers.html#photoLandscape.name: photoLandscape
FulcrumHelpers.html#photoLandscape.summary: Require photo to be taken landscape
FulcrumHelpers.html#photoLandscape.description: Validation for photo orientation, must be called from an ONCHANGE event of a photo field.

FulcrumHelpers.html#photoSetLoc.title: photoSetLoc( event )  {void}
FulcrumHelpers.html#photoSetLoc.name: photoSetLoc
FulcrumHelpers.html#photoSetLoc.description: Sets record location to the location of the first photo taken

FulcrumHelpers.html#popLatLon.description: For use in data event. Sets value of {data_name} to current lat/lon as a string "lat,lon". Alerts if no GPS info.

FulcrumHelpers.html#rows2Summary.name: rows2Summary
FulcrumHelpers.html#rows2Summary.description: Converts an array of objects to an array of summary strings, excluding specified keys. Each summary string lists key-value pairs separated by commas.

FulcrumHelpers.html#setAllRO.title: setAllRO( [ bol [, exc [, sec ] ] ] )  {void}
FulcrumHelpers.html#setAllRO.name: setAllRO
FulcrumHelpers.html#setAllRO.description: Sets all fields to readonly or editable or default, except those in the exclude list or not in the section if specified.

FulcrumHelpers.html#timedProcessingMsg.title: timedProcessingMsg( time )  {void}
FulcrumHelpers.html#timedProcessingMsg.name: timedProcessingMsg
FulcrumHelpers.html#timedProcessingMsg.description: block input into form with an alert message for a set time in milliseconds.

FulcrumHelpers.html#valProcessingMsg.name: valProcessingMsg
FulcrumHelpers.html#valProcessingMsg.description: block input into form with an alert message until a value is present in the specified data name or until a settimeout.

FulcrumHelpers.html#.MLoadRecords.title: MLoadRecords

FulcrumHelpers.html#.MLoadRecords.description: Loads the form schema and creates dictionary to convert form_value keys to data_name keys. This will be modified soon to utilize the new query filtering options in LOADRECORDS.

Helpers.html.title: Helpers
Helpers.html.name: Helpers
Helpers.html.description: For use in any JavaScript project, including Google Apps scripts etc.

Helpers.html#arr2Rem.title: arr2Rem( haystack, needle )  {Array}
Helpers.html#arr2Rem.name: arr2Rem
Helpers.html#arr2Rem.summary: Array too Remove - Return new array with elements removed.
Helpers.html#arr2Rem.description: Remove element OR elements from array, needle can be a single element or an array of elements. ie: Remove data_name string from array of data_names. Return new list of field names. Returns a new array.

Helpers.html#arr2Reversed.title: arr2Reversed( arr )  {Array}
Helpers.html#arr2Reversed.name: arr2Reversed
Helpers.html#arr2Reversed.summary: Array too Reversed - Sorts an array in descending order.
Helpers.html#arr2Reversed.description: Sorts an array of strings, numbers, or dates in descending order. Automatically determines data type of array contents. Returns a new array.

Helpers.html#arr2Sorted.title: arr2Sorted( arr [, asc ] )  {Array}
Helpers.html#arr2Sorted.name: arr2Sorted
Helpers.html#arr2Sorted.summary: Array too Sorted - Sorts an array, defaults to ascending order.
Helpers.html#arr2Sorted.description: Sorts an array of strings, numbers, or dates in ascending or descending order. Defults to ascending order. Automatically determines data type of array contents. Returns a new array.

Helpers.html#arrAnyInArr.title: arrAnyInArr( arr1, arr2 )  {boolean}
Helpers.html#arrAnyInArr.name: arrAnyInArr
Helpers.html#arrAnyInArr.summary: Array Any in Array - Check if any string in one array is in another array.
Helpers.html#arrAnyInArr.description: Returns true if any string in arr1 matches any string in arr2.

Helpers.html#arrCountItems.title: arrCountItems( arr )  {Array.<{item: (string|number), count: number}>}
Helpers.html#arrCountItems.name: arrCountItems
Helpers.html#arrCountItems.summary: Array Count Items - Count occurrences of items in an array.
Helpers.html#arrCountItems.description: Counts the number of occurrences of each unique item in an array and returns an array of objects, each with properties 'item' and 'count', sorted by count descending. Example: ['a','b','a'] => [ { item: 'a', count: 2 }, { item: 'b', count: 1 } ]

Helpers.html#arrListDups.title: arrListDups( arr )  {Array}
Helpers.html#arrListDups.name: arrListDups
Helpers.html#arrListDups.summary: Array List Duplicates - List duplicate values in an array.
Helpers.html#arrListDups.description: Creates an array containing all values that are present in array more then once. Also see arrUnique to filter an array down to only unique values.

Helpers.html#arrRem.title: arrRem( haystack, needle )  {void}
Helpers.html#arrRem.name: arrRem
Helpers.html#arrRem.summary: Array Remove - Remove element from array.
Helpers.html#arrRem.description: Remove element OR elements from array, needle can be a single element or an array of elements. ie: Remove data_name string from array of data_names. Return new list of field names. MUTATES original array.

Helpers.html#arrReverse.title: arrReverse( arr )  {void}
Helpers.html#arrReverse.name: arrReverse
Helpers.html#arrReverse.summary: Array Reverse - Sorts an array in descending order.
Helpers.html#arrReverse.description: Sorts an array of strings, numbers, or dates in descending order. Automatically determines data type of array contents. MUTATES original array.

Helpers.html#arrSort.title: arrSort( arr [, asc ] )  {void}
Helpers.html#arrSort.name: arrSort
Helpers.html#arrSort.summary: Array Sort - Sorts an array, defaults to ascending order.
Helpers.html#arrSort.description: Sorts an array of strings, numbers, or dates in ascending or descending order. Defults to ascending order. Automatically determines data type of array contents. MUTATES original array.

Helpers.html#arrSplice.title: arrSplice( haystack, needle, pos )  {void}
Helpers.html#arrSplice.name: arrSplice
Helpers.html#arrSplice.summary: Array Splice - Add element to array, default to end of array.
Helpers.html#arrSplice.description: Add element to array at position "pos". MUTATES the existing array. ie: Add field name string to list of field names at position "pos". Return new list of field names. MUTATES existing array.

Helpers.html#arrUnique.title: arrUnique( arr )  {Array}
Helpers.html#arrUnique.name: arrUnique
Helpers.html#arrUnique.summary: Array Unique - Filter array to unique values.
Helpers.html#arrUnique.description: Filter an array down to an array of unique values

Helpers.html#dd2dms.title: dd2dms( dd, isLat )  {array}
Helpers.html#dd2dms.name: dd2dms
Helpers.html#dd2dms.description: Converts decimal degrees to Degrees, Minutes, Seconds (DMS) format.

Helpers.html#dms2dd.title: dms2dd( deg, min, sec [, dir ] )  {number}
Helpers.html#dms2dd.name: dms2dd
Helpers.html#dms2dd.description: Converts Degrees, Minutes, Seconds (DMS) to Decimal Degrees. Input direction is optional and defaults to 'N' or 'E' (ie: positive number in DD).

Helpers.html#dn2Title.title: dn2Title( str )  {string}
Helpers.html#dn2Title.name: dn2Title
Helpers.html#dn2Title.summary: data_name too Title - Converts a string with underscores to title case.
Helpers.html#dn2Title.description: Converts a string to title case by replacing '_' with a ' ' and applying capitalization to each word. Use to convert Fulcrum data_name strings to title case.

Helpers.html#dt2iso.title: dt2iso( dt )  {string}
Helpers.html#dt2iso.name: dt2iso
Helpers.html#dt2iso.summary: Date too ISO - Convert Date to ISO string.
Helpers.html#dt2iso.description: Convert javascript date/unix timestamp to ISO string with time and timezone stripped strips time and timezone from ISO string.

Helpers.html#dtAddDays.title: dtAddDays( dt, days )  {Date}
Helpers.html#dtAddDays.name: dtAddDays
Helpers.html#dtAddDays.summary: Date Add Days - Adds days to a date.
Helpers.html#dtAddDays.description: Adds a number of days to a date and returns the new date. Input can be a Date object or a date string.

Helpers.html#dtDaysDiff.title: dtDaysDiff( dt1, dt2 )  {number}
Helpers.html#dtDaysDiff.name: dtDaysDiff
Helpers.html#dtDaysDiff.summary: Date Days Difference - Calculate the difference in days between two dates.
Helpers.html#dtDaysDiff.description: Calculate the difference in days between two dates.

Helpers.html#dtMonthBounds.title: dtMonthBounds( dt )  {Object}
Helpers.html#dtMonthBounds.name: dtMonthBounds
Helpers.html#dtMonthBounds.summary: Date Month Bounds - Get first and last day of month for a given date.
Helpers.html#dtMonthBounds.description: Returns the first and last day of the month for a given date.

Helpers.html#dtStrip.title: dtStrip( str )  {string}
Helpers.html#dtStrip.name: dtStrip
Helpers.html#dtStrip.summary: Date Strip - Strip timezone and time from ISO String date.
Helpers.html#dtStrip.description: Strip timezone and time from ISO date and time in string format ie: '2024-09-09T16:23:47Z' returns '2024-09-09'

Helpers.html#flipKVpair.title: flipKVpair( obj )  {*}
Helpers.html#flipKVpair.name: flipKVpair
Helpers.html#flipKVpair.summary: Flip Key:Value Pair - Flips keys and values in an object.
Helpers.html#flipKVpair.description: Flips keys and values in an object. Object must have unique values. Input is an Object NOT an array of objects.

Helpers.html#formatAddress.title: formatAddress( val )  {string}
Helpers.html#formatAddress.name: formatAddress
Helpers.html#formatAddress.description: Formats a fulcrum address object into a us address formated string.

Helpers.html#fVal.title: fVal( val [, naVal ] )  {string}
Helpers.html#fVal.name: fVal
Helpers.html#fVal.summary: Format Value - Format unknown value to printable String.
Helpers.html#fVal.description: Format unknown value to Merjent standard formatted String. Useful for values returned from Query API or REPEATABLEVALUES. ie: a string '2011-10-05T14:48:00.000Z' returns '011-10-05" ie: an array as a string 'apples,oranges,bananas" returns 'apples, oranges, bananas' This function is intended for values that unknown values that are not returned from a fulcrum field. (for example from an HTTPS request). For values from a fulcrum field use the fldVal method.

Helpers.html#html.title: html( strings, ...vals )  {*}
Helpers.html#html.name: html
Helpers.html#html.summary: Clean HTML - Removes newlines and trims whitespace from template literal.
Helpers.html#html.description: Useful for embedding HTML snippets in JavaScript without extra whitespace or newlines. removes all newline characters (\r and \n). removes any leading or trailing whitespace.

Helpers.html#isBlank.title: isBlank( val )  {boolean}
Helpers.html#isBlank.name: isBlank
Helpers.html#isBlank.description: Check if variable is undefined, null or '' (empty string) OR if it is an Array if it has a length of 0 OR if it is an Object if it has an Object.keys() length of 0

Helpers.html#isDate.title: isDate( val )  {boolean}
Helpers.html#isDate.name: isDate
Helpers.html#isDate.summary: Determines if a value is a valid Date object or a valid date string.
Helpers.html#isDate.description: returns true if val is a Date object or a valid date string.

Helpers.html#isInstance.title: isInstance( obj, ClassConstructor )  {Boolean}
Helpers.html#isInstance.name: isInstance
Helpers.html#isInstance.summary: Checks if object is an instance of a specific class.

Helpers.html#isISOdt.title: isISOdt( str )  {boolean}
Helpers.html#isISOdt.name: isISOdt
Helpers.html#isISOdt.summary: Check if string is in ISO 8601 date format.
Helpers.html#isISOdt.description: Checks if string is in the format of an ISO 8601 date format ie: '2011-10-05T14:48:00.000Z'

Helpers.html#isNumber.title: isNumber( val )  {boolean}
Helpers.html#isNumber.name: isNumber
Helpers.html#isNumber.summary: Determines if a value is a number.
Helpers.html#isNumber.description: Determines if a value is a number (not NaN, not a string).

Helpers.html#iso2dt.title: iso2dt( str )  {Date}
Helpers.html#iso2dt.name: iso2dt
Helpers.html#iso2dt.summary: ISO too Date - Convert ISO to Date.
Helpers.html#iso2dt.description: Convert ISO date in string format to javascript date/unix timestamp. Strips time and timezone if present before conversion.

Helpers.html#padZero.title: padZero( val, length )  {string}
Helpers.html#padZero.name: padZero
Helpers.html#padZero.summary: Add leading zeroes to a number(or string number).
Helpers.html#padZero.description: Pads a number OR string with leading zeroes to reach a specified total length. Returns a string with leading zeroes.

Helpers.html#rows2Sorted.title: rows2Sorted( arr, key [, asc [, type ] ] )  {Array.<Object>}
Helpers.html#rows2Sorted.name: rows2Sorted
Helpers.html#rows2Sorted.summary: Rows too Sorted - Sorts an array of Objects, defaults to ascending order.
Helpers.html#rows2Sorted.description: Sorts an array of objects by a given property, or by value if objects contain only one key:value pair and parameter 'key' is null. Automatically sorts as number if type is 'number' or values are numbers, and as date if type is 'date' or values are valid dates. Returns a new array.

Helpers.html#rowsFind.title: rowsFind( rows, key, val )  {Array.<Object>}
Helpers.html#rowsFind.name: rowsFind
Helpers.html#rowsFind.summary: Rows Find - Find objects in array by property value.
Helpers.html#rowsFind.description: Finds objects with property matching lookup value in an array of objects and returns that object.

Helpers.html#strAfter.title: strAfter( val, search )  {string}
Helpers.html#strAfter.name: strAfter
Helpers.html#strAfter.summary: String After - Return slice AFTER FIRST occurence.
Helpers.html#strAfter.description: Return slice of string AFTER FIRST occurence of search string. Useful for getting middle section of text after underscore in data_name.

Helpers.html#strBefore.title: strBefore( val, search )  {string}
Helpers.html#strBefore.name: strBefore
Helpers.html#strBefore.summary: String Before - Return slice BEFORE FIRST occurence.
Helpers.html#strBefore.description: Return slice of string BEFORE FIRST occurence of search string. Useful for getting prefix of text before first underscore in data_name.

Helpers.html#strProper.title: strProper( word )  {string}
Helpers.html#strProper.name: strProper
Helpers.html#strProper.summary: String Proper - Capitalizes the first character of a word
Helpers.html#strProper.description: Capitalizes the first character of a word and converts the rest to lowercase.

Helpers.html#strSuff.title: strSuff( val, search )  {string}
Helpers.html#strSuff.name: strSuff
Helpers.html#strSuff.summary: String Suffix - Return slice AFTER LAST occurence.
Helpers.html#strSuff.description: Return slice of string AFTER LAST occurence of search string. Useful for getting suffix of text after last underscore in data_name.

MerjentApp.html.title: MerjentApp
MerjentApp.html.name: MerjentApp
MerjentApp.html.description: This class handles common data events in Mejent fulcrum Apps. To turn off fieldLock and completeLock set mApp. mApp.completeLockCondition = [] or mApp.fieldLockCondition = []. To turn off the updateStatus method set mApp.dnSubmit = null

MerjentApp.html#.statusMethods.title: <static> statusMethods :StatusMethods
MerjentApp.html#.statusMethods.name: statusMethods
MerjentApp.html#.statusMethods.description: This is a list of template getStatus() methods. Each one is setup for a set of status values. Most of the changes in status are triggerd by changes in the value of the this.dnSubmit and this.dnReviewed fields. Most methods assume that fields are Y/N fields and a value of 'yes' triggers the change in status. Exceptions are noted.

MerjentApp.html#adminNames.title: adminNames :Array.<string>
MerjentApp.html#adminNames.name: adminNames

MerjentApp.html#adminRoles.name: adminRoles
MerjentApp.html#adminRoles.description: Array of Fulcrum user roles to have "Admin" privleges in this app.

MerjentApp.html#allPhotos.title: allPhotos :Array
MerjentApp.html#allPhotos.name: allPhotos
MerjentApp.html#allPhotos.description: Array of photo names to check for missing captions and exceeding max character limit.

MerjentApp.html#completeLockCondition.name: completeLockCondition
MerjentApp.html#completeLockCondition.description: Array of status values to match for turning on complete record lock. To turn off complete lock use empty array [].

MerjentApp.html#completeLockExclude.title: completeLockExclude :Array.<string>
MerjentApp.html#completeLockExclude.name: completeLockExclude
MerjentApp.html#completeLockExclude.description: Array of data names to exclude from read-only status when complete lock is on.

MerjentApp.html#defaultPermissionLevel.title: defaultPermissionLevel :string
MerjentApp.html#defaultPermissionLevel.name: defaultPermissionLevel
MerjentApp.html#defaultPermissionLevel.summary: The default permission level for users that are not specified as being under a specific permission level.

MerjentApp.html#disableLocationEdit.title: disableLocationEdit :boolean
MerjentApp.html#disableLocationEdit.name: disableLocationEdit

MerjentApp.html#dnCoordinatorInitials.title: dnCoordinatorInitials :string
MerjentApp.html#dnCoordinatorInitials.name: dnCoordinatorInitials
MerjentApp.html#dnCoordinatorInitials.description: Data name of the 'dnCoordinatorInitials' field. Signed with coordinator initials when mApp.dnReviewed gets checked 'yes'

MerjentApp.html#dnDt.title: dnDt :string
MerjentApp.html#dnDt.name: dnDt

MerjentApp.html#dnFollowUp.name: dnFollowUp
MerjentApp.html#dnFollowUp.description: Data name of the follow=up required y/n field.
